70
00:05:06.095 --> 00:05:09.230
There are four major experiments at CERN.

71
00:05:09.230 --> 00:05:11.760
These experiments are LHCb,

72
00:05:11.760 --> 00:05:15.075
ATLAS, ALICE and CMS.

73
00:05:15.075 --> 00:05:16.840
From the previous week,

74
00:05:16.840 --> 00:05:20.235
you know that Large Hadron Collider has

75
00:05:20.235 --> 00:05:24.855
two beams of protons that fly in opposite directions.

76
00:05:24.855 --> 00:05:28.915
Each of these beams are divided into bunches.

77
00:05:28.915 --> 00:05:33.965
Each bunch has about 10 in 11 protons.

78
00:05:33.965 --> 00:05:40.250
Bunches of the beams cross each other inside the detectors.

79
00:05:40.250 --> 00:05:44.010
And there are several proton-proton collisions

80
00:05:44.010 --> 00:05:49.155
are generated inside the detector during the bunch crossing.

81
00:05:49.155 --> 00:05:52.525
The proton-proton collisions produce a lot of

82
00:05:52.525 --> 00:05:57.120
other particles that decay into other particles and so on.

83
00:05:57.120 --> 00:06:00.845
The detectors recognize these particles,

84
00:06:00.845 --> 00:06:05.120
estimates their types, and measures their energies and momentum.

85
00:06:05.120 --> 00:06:12.280
Each bunch crossing with all generated particles is called an event.

86
00:06:12.280 --> 00:06:20.405
There're 40 millions events per seconds generated on Large Hadron Collider at CERN.

87
